<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="polite-adj">polite <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /pə'laɪt/    美 /pə'laɪt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-impolite-rude">1.★ <strong>有礼貌的；有教养的【反: impolite / rude】；客套的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>be polite to sb 
对某人有礼貌</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It is</strong> not <strong>polite to</strong> talk with your mouth full. 
带着满嘴的食物就张嘴说话不礼貌。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a <strong>polite conversation</strong>
客套的交谈</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>politely /pə'laɪtli/ adv <br />
politeness /pə'laɪtnəs/ n [U]   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>After knocking <strong><em>_</em></strong>__ (礼貌地) at the door, the applicant entered the office of the general manager.  （2015 陕西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. politely  </p></div>